        [
          "Vampire Archaeologist",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "JA"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Like most Gangrel, your Embrace came as a surprise and you were rather left to your own devices for your first few nights. As you figured out how to survive, you became aware of the different factions of vampires, particularly the Camarilla and the Sabbat. After some study and reflection, you decided to join neither sect and would instead strike out on your own. Your curiosity as to your own origins has made you want to understand the origin of all vampires. You've also heard rumors of something called Gehenna, which sounds terrifying. As such, you've devoted your unlife to uncovering the secrets and lore which most others would prefer remain hidden. This hasn't earned you many friends - after discovering Hardestadt's secret, he sent Theo Bell to try and kill you. You got away, but you know it's only a matter of time before he tries again. You also have to keep your head up for your childe, Marie, who resents her Embrace. Recently, you've heard of an important artifact which has surfaced in Los Angeles and is of obvious vampiric origin. You have to know more!"
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Unknown",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "http://whitewolf.wikia.com/wiki/Beckett",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Gangrel - Animalistic Beast"
        ],
        [
          "Embrace Date:",
          "1704.0",
          "Embrace Location:",
          "London",
          "",
          "Generation",
          "Pretender Elder 8"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Who You Know",
          "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        ],
        [
          "Sebastian La Croix (Ventrue) (Andy Milder)",
          "The Ventrue Prince of Los Angeles. While you're not a Camarilla member, it's worthwhile to stay on his good side for as long as you want to stay in the city."
        ],
        [
          "Smiling Jack (Brujah) (John DiMaggio)",
          "A local Anarch leader who spends most of his time downtown at a place called the Last Round. If you want to get in good with the Anarchs, you'll need to get Smiling Jack and his ally Nines Rodriguez on your side."
        ],
        [
          "Jeanette Voerman (Malkavian) (Grey DeLisle)",
          "She and her (broodmate? sire? you're unsure of the exact nature of their relationship) Therese run a club together in Santa Monica. Though they're often at each other's throats, they're a formidable team when they work together. The club would be useful for you to start to build your base within the city."
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "You have come to LA pursuing rumors of an artifact called the Ankaran Sarcophagus. It's entirely likely that a sleeping Methuselah, or even Antediluvan, is in there. Find out what you can about what's inside before you risk opening it (and if it is an ancient, don't let Sebastian eat it)"
        ],
        [
          "You've heard rumors of an illegal Embrace. The sire was killed, but the childe is now some kind of lackey or agent for pretty much everyone in the city - and they're surprisingly effective. Help the new childe if you can."
        ],
        [
          "Cathayans have set up shop in Los Angeles, led by a woman named Ming-Xiao. Make contact, and see if you can come to some kind of deal for information exchange."
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Player Amended History",
          "",
          "Date Submited"
        ]
      ],
